properties.headline: Dense Fog Advisory issued January 23 at 6:52AM PST until January 23 at 10:00AM PST by NWS Hanford CA
properties.description:
* WHAT...Visibilities in dense fog ranging from 800 feet to as
low as 200 feet.

* WHERE...Southern San Joaquin Valley.

* WHEN...Until 10 AM PST this morning.

* IMPACTS...Hazardous driving conditions due to low visibility.

* ADDITIONAL DETAILS...Highways affected include, but are not
limited to Highway 99 and Highway 58.
properties.instruction:
If driving, slow down, use low beam headlights, and keep plenty
of distance between your vehicle and the vehicle in front of you.

NWSheadline: DENSE FOG ADVISORY IN EFFECT UNTIL 10 AM PST THIS MORNING
